Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function, possibly diabetic nephropathy or another renal pathology. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, but urine findings indicate possible transient hyperglycemia or renal glycosuria. Metabolic acidosis is suggested by low COâ‚‚ and high chloride. Urine is cloudy and brown, but no infection markers are present. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
